<section class="section text-white text-center" style="background-color: var(--primary-green);">
  <div class="container">
    <h1 class="display-5 fw-bold">History and Development</h1>
    <p class="lead mb-4" style="max-width: 700px; margin: 0 auto;">
      The Solar Energy Society of Nigeria (SESN) was founded in 1980 to promote the widespread utilization of solar and other renewable energy technologies across the country.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container">

    

    <!-- FORMATION -->
    <div class="card shadow-sm p-4 mb-4">
      <h5 class="fw-bold mb-3">Formation and Early Vision</h5>

      <p class="text-muted">
        The Solar Energy Society of Nigeria (SESN) was established as a professional and academic platform to promote the development, research, and application of solar energy technologies in Nigeria.
      </p>

      <p class="text-muted">
        The Society emerged in response to the growing need for sustainable and renewable energy solutions to address Nigeria's persistent energy challenges.
      </p>

      <p class="text-muted">
        Founded by engineers, scientists, researchers, policymakers, and renewable energy advocates, SESN recognizes Nigeria’s vast solar potential due to its location in the tropical region with abundant sunlight throughout the year.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- GROWTH -->
    <div class="card shadow-sm p-4 mb-4">
      <h5 class="fw-bold mb-3">Growth and Development</h5>

      <ul class="text-muted">
        <li>Organization of national and international conferences</li>
        <li>Partnership with universities and research institutions</li>
        <li>Collaboration with government agencies</li>
        <li>Support for rural solar electrification projects</li>
        <li>Encouragement of youth participation in renewable energy</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- IMPACT -->
    <div class="card shadow-sm p-4 mb-4">
      <h5 class="fw-bold mb-3">Contribution to National Development</h5>

      <p class="text-muted">
        SESN has played a significant role in promoting clean and sustainable energy solutions across Nigeria. The Society has contributed to climate change mitigation, encouraged local innovation, and built professional capacity through training and certification programs.
      </p>

      <p class="text-muted">
        Through advocacy and research, SESN continues to support Nigeria's transition toward renewable energy and improved energy access in underserved communities.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- FUTURE -->
    <div class="card shadow-sm p-4">
      <h5 class="fw-bold mb-3">Present and Future Outlook</h5>

      <p class="text-muted">
        Today, the Solar Energy Society of Nigeria remains committed to expanding solar adoption, strengthening research and innovation, forming global partnerships, and empowering young engineers and entrepreneurs in the renewable energy sector.
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>